IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: PROVIDE QUALITY COMPREHENSIVE BEHAVIORAL HEALTH SERVICES TO RESIDENTS IN CLALLAM COUNTY.
IRS990.MissionDesc: PENINSULA BEHAVIORAL HEALTH IS CLALLAM COUNTY'S PRIMARY RESOURCE FOR BEHAVIORAL HEALTH AND CO-OCCURRING SUBSTANCE USE DISORDER COUNSELING. PBH BELIEVES THAT EVERYONE, DESERVES ACCESS TO QUALITY BEHAVIORAL HEALTHCARE. PBH IS PROUD TO MAKE BEHAVIORAL HEALTHCARE AND THERAPY AFFORDABLE AND ACCESSIBLE TO OUR COMMUNITY. IN 2020, PBH WAS AWARDED AN EXPANSION GRANT FROM SAMSHA, TRANSFORMING US INTO A CCBHC.
IRS990.Desc: CLINICAL OUTPATIENT SERVICES - A WIDE RANGE OF CARING SERVICES IS AVAILABLE TO MEET THE NEEDS OF PERSONS WITH SERIOUS MENTAL ILLNESS OR SUBSTANCE USE DISORDER. STAFF WITH A VARIETY OF SPECIALTIES OFFER EVALUATIONS, THERAPY AND PREVENTION STRATEGIES TO SUPPORT INDIVIDUALS IN THE COMMUNITY AT CRITICAL STAGES OF LIFE. KEY SERVICES INCLUDE ADULT OUTPATIENT THERAPY, COMMUNITY SUPPORT SERVICES, CARE NAVIGATION, YOUTH OUTPATIENT SERVICES, INCLUDING WISE SERVICES AND EVIDENCE BASED PRACTICES.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: MEDICAL SERVICES - PSYCHIATRIC EVALUATIONS, CONSULTATION WITH PRIMARY CARE PROVIDERS AND PSYCHIATRIC MEDICATION MONITORING.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: CLINICAL INTENSIVE SERVICES - CRISIS INTERVENTION SERVICES, INCLUDING CRISIS RESPITE CARE, COMMUNITY RESPONSE TO CRISIS CALLS. SERVICES INCLUDE COMMUNITY OUTREACH SERVICES TO THOSE UNHOUSED IN THE COMMUNITY.

ProgSrvcAccomActyOtherGrp.Desc: RESIDENTIAL SERVICES - THE QUALITY OF LIFE FOR MENTALLY ILL CITIZENS AND CAREGIVERS IS ENHANCED THROUGH RESIDENTIAL OPTIONS THAT INTEGRATE RECOVERY WITH PRACTICAL INDEPENDENT LIVING SKILLS. ADULT TRANSITION HOMES AND APARTMENTS WITH SUPPORTED LIVING ARRANGEMENTS ARE OFFERED WHEN LESS THAN A SUPERVISED ENVIRONMENT ARE REQUIRED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: FUNDS ARE HELD BY CLALLAM COMMUNITY FOUNDATION, CANNOT BE SPENT WITHOUT PENINSULA BEHAVIORAL HEALTH APPROVAL AND CURRENTLY ARE NOT BEING DRAWN FROM. THE INTENDED USE OF THE FUNDS IS TO HELP SUPPORT PROGRAM OPERATIONS.

THE ORGANIZATION IS NOT SUBJECT TO INCOME TAX, BECAUSE IT IS A TAX-EXEMPT ORGANIZATION UNDER INTERNAL REVENUE CODE SECTION 501(C)(3). ACCORDINGLY, NO PROVISION FOR INCOME TAX IS INCLUDED IN THESE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. FOR THE 2023 AND 2022 FINANCIAL STATEMENTS, THE ORGANIZATION HAS ACCOUNTED FOR UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS WHEREBY THE EFFECT OF THE UNCERTAINTY WOULD BE RECORDED IF THE OUTCOME WAS CONSIDERED PROBABLE AND WAS REASONABLY ESTIMABLE. AS OF JUNE 30, 2023 AND 2022, THE ORGANIZATION HAD NOT IDENTIFIED ANY UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS REQUIRING ACCRUAL OR DISCLOSURE.

GrantsOtherAsstToIndivInUSGrp.GrantTypeTxt: PATIENT MEDICATION, TRANSPORTATION AND LIVING ASSISTANCE

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: FUNDS ARE PROVIDED TO INDIGENT PATIENTS WHO ARE IN NEED OF ASSISTANCE WITH PAYING FOR PRESCRIBED MEDICATIONS, TRANSPORTATION AND OTHER LIVING NECESSITIES. SUBSTANTIATION IS REQUIRED TO BE PROVIDED BEFORE FUNDS ARE GIVEN.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE PREPARED FORM 990 AND SCHEDULE B IS REVIEWED FIRST BY THE CHIEF FINANCIAL OFFICER, THEN THE CHIEF EXECUTIVE OFFICER FOR RECOMMENDATION TO THE BOARD FOR FORMAL APPROVAL BEFORE FILING WITH THE IRS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ALL BOARD MEMBERS SHALL SUBMIT, UPON ASSUMING THEIR POSITIONS AND THEREAFTER, ANNUAL IN WRITING TO THE PRESIDENT OF THE PENINSULA BEHAVIORAL HEALTH BOARD, A LIST OF ALL BUSINESSES OR OTHER ORGANIZATIONS OF WHICH HE OR SHE IS AN OFFICER, MEMBER, OWNER OR EMPLOYEE, OR FOR WHICH HE OR SHE ACTS AS AN AGENCY WITH WHICH PENINSULA BEHAVIORAL HEALTH HAS ENTERED, OR MIGHT REASONABLY IN THE FUTURE ENTER INTO A RELATIONSHIP OR A TRANSACTION WHERE PENINSULA BEHAVIORAL HEALTH MIGHT COMPETE AGAINST SUCH ORGANIZATION AND IN WHICH THE BOARD MEMBER OR EXECUTIVE WOULD HAVE CONFLICTING INTERESTS. THE PRESIDENT OF THE BOARD SHALL BECOME FAMILIAR WITH THE STATEMENTS OF ALL BOARD MEMBERS IN ORDER TO GUIDE HIS OR HER CONDUCT IN CHAIRING MEETINGS SHOULD A CONFLICT ARISE. WHEN ANY MATTERS COMES BEFORE THE BOARD AND RAISES THE ISSUE OF A CONFLICT FOR BOARD MEMBERS, THE AFFECTED BOARD MEMBER SHALL MAKE KNOWN THE POTENTIAL CONFLICT, WHETHER DISCLOSED BY WRITTEN STATEMENT OR NOT. DISCLOSURE SHOULD BE MADE AS SOON AS POSSIBLE AS PRACTICABLE AS TO AVOID ANY ADVERTENT HARM TO PENINSULA BEHAVIORAL HEALTH. THE MEMBER SHALL ANSWER ANY QUESTIONS THAT MIGHT BE ASKED BY OTHER BOARD MEMBERS OR LEGAL COUNSEL. THE PRESIDENT, WITH THE ASSISTANCE OF LEGAL COUNSEL, MAY REQUEST THE BOARD MEMBER TO: 1. REFRAIN FROM PARTICIPATING IN THE DISCUSSION INVOLVING THE CONFLICT. 2. LEAVE THE ROOM WHILE THE MATTER IS BEING DISCUSSED. 3. REFRAIN FROM VOTING ON ANY MATTER RELATED TO THE ISSUE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: CEO COMPENSATION IS REVIEWED ANNUALLY UTILIZING SALARY SURVEY DATA SPECIFIC TO OUR INDUSTRY. THE HR DIRECTOR REVIEWS AND MAKES RECOMMENDATIONS FOR ANY CHANGES. THE BOARD PROVIDES A PERFORMANCE EVALUATION FOR THE CEO ALONG WITH APPROVING COMPENSATION INCREASES AND BONUSES. OTHER OFFICER AND KEY EMPLOYEE COMPENSATION INCREASES ARE DETERMINED ANNUALLY DURING THE BUDGETING PROCESS, ALONG WITH OTHER STAFF COMPENSATION INCREASES, AND APPROVED BY THE BOARD VIA THE BUDGET APPROVAL PROCESS. PERFORMANCE EVALUATIONS ARE COMPLETED AND THEN RAISE PERCENTAGES DETERMINED BY EXECUTIVE MANAGEMENT, STAYING WITHIN BUDGETED GUIDELINES APPROVED DURING THE BUDGET CYCLE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 18
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COPIES OF THE ORGANIZATION'S FORM 990 AND FORM 1023 APPLICATION ARE MAINTAINED IN THE OFFICE OF THE CFO. THE DOCUMENTS ARE AVAILABLE FOR PUBLIC INSPECTION DURING REGULAR BUSINESS HOURS BY REQUESTING THE RECEPTIONIST TO CALL EXTENSION 199, OR BY MAIL DIRECTED TO THE CFO, 118 E. 8TH ST., PORT ANGELES, WA 98362 OR BY FAXING A REQUEST TO THE CFO AT FAX NUMBER (360) 457-0493.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COPIES OF THE AUDITED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE MAINTAINED IN THE OFFICE OF THE CFO. THE INFORMATION IS AVAILABLE FOR PUBLIC INSPECTION DURING BUSINESS HOURS OF 9:00 A.M. TO 4:00 P.M. BY REQUESTING THE RECEPTIONIST TO CALL EXTENSION 199, OR BY MAIL DIRECTED TO THE CFO, 118 E. 8TH ST., PORT ANGELES, WA 98362 OR BY FAXING A REQUEST TO THE CFO AT FAX NUMBER (360) 457-0493. THE ORGANIZATION'S GOVERNING DOCUMENTS ARE MADE AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC BY CONTACTING THE CEO'S OFFICE AT (360) 457-0431, EXT. 154. THE ORGANIZATION'S CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY IS MADE AVAILABLE FOR PUBLIC VIEWING AND IS POSTED ON THE RECEPTION AREA BULLETIN BOARD.
